Program: Discovery
Title: Restoration Science - art
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryrm
Last Broadcast Date: 22 August 2004
How science is helping the conservation and restoration of works of art. The programme explores how science is contributing to the understanding, conservation and restoration of works of art from the Renaissance period. Featuring the restoration of the work 'Patient Griselda' by Jill Dunkerton at the National Gallery in London. Show less